http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Freak-tragedy/article14024378.ece

Two brothers were electrocuted early on Wednesday when they came in contact with an electric fencing they had arranged around their fields to keep wild boars at bay.The Mudigubba police said that Boya Narasimhulu (38) and Boya Tirupal (35) of Sankepalli village in Mudigubba mandal went to water their groundnut fields on the outskirts of the village. Narasimhulu seemed to have accidentally come in contact with the electric fencing, and Tirupal too was electrocuted trying to save him, the police said.The bodies have been sent for a post-mortem examination.